Belarus Ruble Drops 23% on Streets of Minsk After Limits Lifted, Banks Say

-- B y   A l e x   K u d r y t s k i
-- 
2011-05-11T10:02:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/belarus-ruble-drops-23-on-streets-of-minsk-after-limits-lifted-banks-say.html
Belarus’s ruble is trading 23 percent
weaker against the dollar on the streets of Minsk than the
central bank’s official exchange rate, a survey of banks in the
capital shows.  The ruble is trading at 3,991 per dollar, according to the
median mid price of five banks’ quotes in Minsk today. The
National Bank of the Republic of Belarus’s official rate is set
at 3,061 per dollar for today, according to its web site.  Belinvestbank, BPS Bank and Fransabank SAL are all buying
dollars for 3,990 and selling at 4,000, according to currency
display boards in their branches and quotes on their web sites.
Sombelbank is buying at 3,960 and selling at 4,000, while RRB
Bank is buying at 3,980 and selling at 4,000, their boards
showed today.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emma O’Brien at 
 eobrien6@bloomberg.net  